f=Engineering/nova/custom/mobile-verification/SKILL.md · in=mobile-verification nova proves mobile app actually works real devices, across OSes, before ships place you can't easily recall from. It's department's "agents say done; device tells truth" mobile: simulator says layout fine app crashes three-year-old Android; emulator says flow works permission dialog blocks iOS. Real-device evidence trustworthy kind. · p=Mobile failure modes web doesn't: device fragmentation (screen sizes, versions, chips), permission flows, offline behavior, battery/memory constraints, platform gestures. verification ran developer's simulator verified almost nothing. Because mobile can't roll back (app-store-release-discipline), pre-ship verification carries even weight mia's. · wu=Triggers (only `mobile_active`): "test app," "verify devices," "does work Android/iOS," "did render device," pre-submission (release discipline requires it), any mobile change. · st:/ Protocol=`[GATE: mobile_active?] A mobile change/release \· -> REAL DEVICES, BOTH OSes: a representative matrix (OS versions, screen sizes, low-end + high-end) \· the simulator/emulator is a first pass, NEVER the verdict \· -> CRITICAL FLOWS: run them on device (like quinn's release gate, mobile edition) \· -> MOBILE-SPECIFIC: permissions, offline behavior, background/foreground, rotation, deep links` · in=**Check switch.** `mobile_active` false dormant. **Real devices, OSes, real matrix.** Test actual iOS Android hardware across representative range versions, screen sizes, low-end high-end. simulator first pass; verdict comes devices. Device fragmentation mobile bugs hide. **Critical flows device.** operator-defined critical journeys run device (quinn's release-gate discipline, mobile edition) unit tests, simulator. **Mobile-specific checks.** Permission grant/deny flows, offline flaky-network behavior (offline-sync-discipline), background/foreground/kill transitions, rotation, deep links, back button (Android). mobile-only failure modes. **Integrity device.** dev's integrity block, mobile edition: real data mock, real API calls stubs, placeholder screen shipped "done." screenshot working simulator fake data exactly false "done" catches. **Evidence, gate.** Verdicts carry device result screenshot/recording evidence, "works machine." feeds quinn's gate hard precondition app-store submission (you can't recall bad release). · of=`## Mobile Verification: [change/release] — [mobile_active ✓] \· Device matrix: [devices \· OS versions \· screen sizes tested] \· Critical flows on device: [PASS/FAIL per flow] \· Mobile-specific: [permissions \· offline \· lifecycle \· rotation \· deep links \· back button] \· Integrity: [real data ✓ \· real API ✓ \· no placeholder-as-done]` · pr=**Real devices, OSes, real matrix** simulator first pass, never verdict., **Critical flows device** quinn's release gate, mobile edition., **Mobile-specific failure modes** permissions, offline, lifecycle, rotation, deep links, back button., **Integrity device** real data API, placeholder-as-done (dev §0)., **Evidence, "works simulator"** device/OS/screenshot it's verdict., **Weightier web verification** because mobile can't roll back. · f=`mobile_active` false → dormant., device farm widest real-device set available emulator breadth, labeled fidelity; recommend device-testing connector stack-profile; never ship emulator-only evidence., Can't reproduce device-specific bug it's still finding (device fragmentation real); narrow device/OS file it, don't dismiss "works elsewhere." · b:with Other Skills=**quinn/browser-verification**: web analogue; mobile counterpart feeding gate., **mia/frontend-verification**: sibling discipline, web device; shared integrity rule (dev §0)., **app-store-release-discipline** (sibling): requires pass before submission (no recall after)., **offline-sync-discipline** (sibling): offline behavior core verification target., **quinn/regression-map**: device-specific fragilities become mapped entries.